77
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:03,875
[whimpers]

78
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:12,542
Anyway.

79
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:16,458
I'm Iwashimizu Sumiaki.
It's a pleasure to meet you.

80
00:05:16,542 --> 00:05:19,667
Yeah, whatever. I'm Gion.

81
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,000
[GION sighs]

82
00:05:35,208 --> 00:05:36,625
[GION]
Why're you following me?

83
00:05:36,709 --> 00:05:37,917
[IWASHIMIZU]
Sorry!

84
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,000
I just hate walking alone--
is that all right?

85
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:54,291
Oh, hey, volleyball!

86
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:55,625
[GIRL 1C]
Awesome!

87
00:05:57,375 --> 00:05:58,875
[BOY 1A] How far do you
think we're gonna get

88
00:05:58,959 --> 00:06:00,792
in this year's preliminaries?

89
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:04,000
--[IWASHIMIZU] Pardon--
--[GION] Listen--

90
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:06,166
[IWASHIMIZU]
My bad. Go ahead.

91
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:08,625
[GION] So. When you
picked me up earlier,

92
00:06:08,709 --> 00:06:11,792
something occurred to me.

93
00:06:11,875 --> 00:06:13,041
You're a really a big guy.

94
00:06:13,125 --> 00:06:15,875
You can see more,
and you can do more, too.

95
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:18,166
And you wanna know something?

96
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:20,208
--[GION yells]
--[IWASHIMIZU yelps]

97
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:22,417
[GION]
That... pisses me off!

98
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,875
Dude, tell me your secret.

99
00:06:23,959 --> 00:06:25,750
What kinda food
do I have to eat?

100
00:06:25,834 --> 00:06:27,333
How many gallons of milk
do I have to drink

101
00:06:27,417 --> 00:06:28,583
to get as big as you?

102
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:30,000
Um...

103
00:06:30,083 --> 00:06:31,709
Well, at home, I normally
just drink hot barley tea!

104
00:06:31,792 --> 00:06:33,709
[GION] So you're sayin'
I need to drink tea, too?

105
00:06:33,792 --> 00:06:35,083
Well, no.

106
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:37,125
Actually, I think milk would
be better for growing.

107
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:40,375
[GION] Are you makin' fun
of me right now, tree trunk?

108
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:45,750
If there's one thing I hate,
it's people givin' me crap

109
00:06:45,834 --> 00:06:46,834
'cause I'm short.

110
00:06:46,917 --> 00:06:49,750
People think I wear
kids' clothes!

111
00:06:49,834 --> 00:06:52,333
Girls don't wanna date me!

112
00:06:52,417 --> 00:06:53,583
And grown men are the worst!

113
00:06:53,667 --> 00:06:56,500
They treat me like a baby!

114
00:06:56,583 --> 00:07:00,041
They all look down on me,
just 'cause I'm little.

115
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:00,959
And you?

116
00:07:01,041 --> 00:07:02,166
I hate you most of all

117
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:04,375
'cause you're a big,
giant, clueless oaf!

118
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:05,583
[gasps]

119
00:07:12,375 --> 00:07:13,583
--Uh--
--[footsteps]

120
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:16,000
[HACHIOJI]
Iwashimizu!

121
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:17,583
[yelps]

122
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:20,875
What's the problem, buddy?
How come you're runnin' away?

123
00:07:20,959 --> 00:07:22,250
Huh?

124
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,667
Oh, Hachioji, it's you.

125
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:27,500
Dude. You're even
bigger than before!

126
00:07:27,583 --> 00:07:29,417
I still can't believe
you're enrolled here.

127
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,208
It's awesome! And guess what?

128
00:07:31,291 --> 00:07:32,500
Dude. We're besties now.

129
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:36,959
All year long.

130
00:07:37,041 --> 00:07:38,709
Huh?

131
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:40,625
[GION]
Get the hell off me, you jerk!

132
00:07:40,709 --> 00:07:43,291
Did you just give
birth? [laughs]

133
00:07:44,709 --> 00:07:46,667
[HACHIOJI]
That wasn't a short joke, okay?

134
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:49,959
I legitimately thought you were
Iwashimizu's newborn child.

135
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:51,417
Shut up!

136
00:07:53,875 --> 00:07:55,583
So, freshman, you got a name?

137
00:07:55,667 --> 00:07:56,792
Tch.

138
00:07:58,625 --> 00:08:01,542
I'm Gion Kenji.

139
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:03,917
Well, Gion.
Hope you're not busy.

140
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,834
Cause if you're free,
you should watch us practice.

141
00:08:05,917 --> 00:08:08,000
We're about to start.

142
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:10,166
[GION]
Hm?

143
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:11,417
Practice?

144
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,208
Is this guy in a club
or somethin' like that?

145
00:08:13,291 --> 00:08:14,291
Huh?

146
00:08:14,375 --> 00:08:18,208
Oh, come on, you
haven't told him yet?

147
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:22,875
Uh... Well, it's...

148
00:08:22,959 --> 00:08:24,583
...rugby.

149
00:08:37,291 --> 00:08:39,542
[GION] So... What the
heck is "rugby" anyway?

150
00:08:39,625 --> 00:08:41,125
Wait. Are you for real?

151
00:08:41,208 --> 00:08:45,333
[HACHIOJI laughs] Wow, you don't
know much of anything, do ya?

152
00:08:45,417 --> 00:08:47,291
If you're gonna play
with us, you'll hafta learn.

153
00:08:47,375 --> 00:08:49,000
That's for sure.

154
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:52,375
[GION]
I'm not here to play with you.

155
00:08:52,458 --> 00:08:54,583
For all I know, you guys're
a bunch of losers.

156
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:56,500
So don't get any ideas!

157
00:08:56,583 --> 00:08:59,083
[laughs] Whatever you say, Gion.

158
00:08:59,166 --> 00:09:00,500
Whatever you say.

159
00:09:00,583 --> 00:09:02,917
But I think you might
change your mind.

160
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:08,166
Rugby's a fun sport. And once
you start, you can't stop.

161
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:13,583
And the best part is,
anyone can be the star.

162
00:09:13,667 --> 00:09:14,959
Even me?

163
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:17,959
[HACHIOJI]
Even you, Gion. You'll see.

164
00:09:22,834 --> 00:09:26,000
Hey, tree trunk.
The rules--what are they?

165
00:09:26,083 --> 00:09:27,959
What? Uh...

166
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,083
[GION]
What's wrong with the ball?

167
00:09:34,166 --> 00:09:35,417
It's not even round.

168
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:38,458
[gasps] You're joking, right?

169
00:09:38,542 --> 00:09:40,917
Look. Something's
about to happen.

170
00:09:42,041 --> 00:09:43,667
Oh. Yeah.

171
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,875
It looks like they're
about to play a mock game.

172
00:09:45,959 --> 00:09:47,291
Just watch.

173
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:53,834
[GION]
So what's the deal?

174
00:09:53,917 --> 00:09:55,208
Is it kinda like soccer?

175
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:56,583
[IWASHIMIZU]
No, not really.

176
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:58,500
You have to run the ball
past the goalposts

177
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:00,417
on either end of the field.

178
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:04,625
Whoa!

179
00:10:04,709 --> 00:10:07,208
He just pummeled him--
that can't be legal!

180
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:09,458
Actually, no, it is.

181
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:12,417
You try to steal the ball,
violently if need be.

182
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:14,083
Big guys like me
have an advantage,

183
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:17,500
so they tried recruiting me
back in middle school.

184
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:19,166
Of course, a whole
lot has happened

185
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:21,709
in between then and now.

186
00:10:21,792 --> 00:10:25,291
[MIYUKI laughs]
Oh, man, you're really huge!

187
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:32,542
Well, it looks like fun to me.

188
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:34,792
[gasps]

189
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:36,792
You don't understand,
it's not all about fun.

190
00:10:36,875 --> 00:10:37,750
Rugby is one of the most

191
00:10:37,834 --> 00:10:39,834
dangerous sports
out there, Gion!

192
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:42,709
[GION]
Who cares?

193
00:10:42,792 --> 00:10:46,458
My dad and my brother
are both man-mountains.

194
00:10:46,542 --> 00:10:49,625
Not me. I'm small.

195
00:10:49,709 --> 00:10:54,291
When we fought, I got my
butt kicked every time.

196
00:10:54,375 --> 00:10:56,333
Lookin' at all these
massive guys...

197
00:10:56,417 --> 00:10:58,792
If I could steal
the ball from them...

198
00:10:58,875 --> 00:11:01,458
...that would be awesome.

199
00:11:03,709 --> 00:11:05,166
[GION]
But...

200
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:09,041
...they're so much bigger and
stronger than I'll ever be.

201
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:11,583
If I did try to join the team,

202
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:14,500
they'd squash me
like a freakin' bug.

203
00:11:18,667 --> 00:11:20,500
That's not true at all.

204
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:24,625
[IWASHIMIZU] Sure, lots of
rugby players are really big.

205
00:11:24,709 --> 00:11:27,625
But, trust me.
Size isn't everything.

206
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:31,125
[IWASHIMIZU]
Look closely.

207
00:11:31,208 --> 00:11:33,333
Big guys, small guys, fat guys,

208
00:11:33,417 --> 00:11:36,000
skinny guys, too--all
different types and shapes.

209
00:11:36,083 --> 00:11:37,542
All with their own
unique skills.

210
00:11:37,625 --> 00:11:40,041
[RUGBY PLAYERS grunting]

211
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:42,041
[IWASHIMIZU]
There are no star strikers.

212
00:11:42,125 --> 00:11:44,250
No power hitters either.

213
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:48,625
[IWASHIMIZU]
If you're holding the ball,

214
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:50,667
then you're the star.

215
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:57,041
[whistle blows]

216
00:12:00,542 --> 00:12:02,875
Well? What'd ya think?

217
00:12:02,959 --> 00:12:04,583
Fun, right?

218
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:06,917
That's the coolest thing
I've seen in my whole life!

219
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:10,000
[HACHIOJI]
Sweet. Glad you liked it!

220
00:12:10,083 --> 00:12:13,667
Hm... I think you'll work
best as a half-scrum.

221
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:16,041
Because you're small.
Then again,

222
00:12:16,125 --> 00:12:19,625
I bet you're pretty quick
so you might do well as a wing.

223
00:12:19,709 --> 00:12:24,709
Well, whaddaya say?
You wanna join the Rugby Team?

224
00:12:24,792 --> 00:12:27,041
[GION] If you're that
desperate for me to join,

225
00:12:27,125 --> 00:12:30,417
how can I say, "no"?

226
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:33,917
I'll knock the crap
outta everybody!

227
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,834
[laughs] That's the
kinda attitude we like!

228
00:12:36,917 --> 00:12:39,542
I have a feeling you're gonna
fit in here just fine!

229
00:12:39,625 --> 00:12:41,333
All right! Wait up.

230
00:12:41,417 --> 00:12:43,834
Where are you off to, man?
I need you to teach me how to--

231
00:12:43,917 --> 00:12:46,709
[IWASHIMIZU]
Listen. I'm sorry. I really am.

232
00:12:46,792 --> 00:12:48,375
But I'm not interested.

233
00:12:48,458 --> 00:12:50,750
What? Well, why not?

234
00:12:50,834 --> 00:12:52,500
Because.

235
00:12:52,583 --> 00:12:53,959
Bye.

236
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:12,250
[HACHIOJI]
There's no practice today.

237
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,834
[GION]
What?! Why?

238
00:13:14,917 --> 00:13:17,208
[HACHIOJI]
'Cause we're recruiting.

239
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:18,834
Then what are you doing in here?

240
00:13:18,917 --> 00:13:20,834
Guarding the base.

241
00:13:20,917 --> 00:13:22,792
Who knows, a prospective
rugby player might

242
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:25,083
walk through that
door any minute.

243
00:13:25,166 --> 00:13:26,709
But I wanna get started!

244
00:13:26,792 --> 00:13:27,875
Right now!

245
00:13:27,959 --> 00:13:29,792
That's not gonna happen, Gion.

246
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:33,166
I do appreciate your
eagerness though.

247
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:36,291
And I'd appreciate it even more
if you got offa my desk.

248
00:13:36,375 --> 00:13:38,166
[GION growls]

249
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,750
[GION]
I'll teach myself!

250
00:13:39,834 --> 00:13:42,583
[HACHIOJI]
Gion, hold on a sec! Come back!

251
00:13:47,959 --> 00:13:49,792
[HACHIOJI]
Hey, Sekizan.

252
00:13:49,875 --> 00:13:51,959
How did it go? Any bites?

253
00:13:52,041 --> 00:13:55,125
Three guys. Only one
of 'em's played before.

254
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:56,834
[HACHIOJI]
Wow! Nice work!

255
00:13:56,917 --> 00:13:58,625
I was hopin' to run
into that big freshman

256
00:13:58,709 --> 00:14:02,375
you told me about,
but no such luck.

257
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:03,500
[GION]
Uh--

258
00:14:03,583 --> 00:14:06,625
Who are you? Hachi,
you know this guy?

259
00:14:06,709 --> 00:14:07,792
[gasps]

260
00:14:07,875 --> 00:14:10,750
[HACHIOJI]
Gion. A freshman. He wants in.

261
00:14:10,834 --> 00:14:12,166
[SEKIZAN]
Hm?

262
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:17,041
He's small. Too small, right?

263
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:20,875
[SEKIZAN] I have an idea
about practice tomorrow.

264
00:14:20,959 --> 00:14:23,166
Once we're done introducing
the new players,

265
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:24,166
I think we should focus on--

266
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:26,583
[GION]
Small, eh?

267
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:30,458
Small?! I'll show
you small, jerk!

268
00:14:30,542 --> 00:14:32,709
[GION yelps]

269
00:14:32,792 --> 00:14:34,875
[GION grunts]

270
00:14:37,792 --> 00:14:39,125
[SEKIZAN]
He's light, too.

271
00:14:39,208 --> 00:14:41,291
Ow!

272
00:14:41,375 --> 00:14:44,583
Gion, that was not a
smart move at all, bud.

273
00:14:44,667 --> 00:14:46,041
This is Sekizan.

274
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:50,667
He's the strongest guy
on the Rugby Team.

275
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,166
Hey.

276
00:14:52,250 --> 00:14:54,792
Big man, was that some kinda
rugby move you pulled on me?

277
00:14:54,875 --> 00:14:55,917
A what?

278
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,750
Uh, he's new.

279
00:14:57,834 --> 00:14:59,709
He doesn't know anything yet.

280
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:05,125
[SEKIZAN] Listen, bro,
I'm sorry I threw you.

281
00:15:05,208 --> 00:15:06,291
That wasn't cool.

282
00:15:06,375 --> 00:15:08,709
Could you maybe not
sit on the table?

283
00:15:08,792 --> 00:15:11,834
[GION] I attacked you. So it's
like five percent my fault.

284
00:15:11,917 --> 00:15:13,083
Just five percent?

285
00:15:13,166 --> 00:15:15,458
[sighs] Listen, that "maneuver"

286
00:15:15,542 --> 00:15:18,458
you were askin' us
about's called a tackle.

287
00:15:21,542 --> 00:15:23,917
Awesome!

288
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,166
Please teach me your
genius ways, master!

289
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:33,583
You talk way too much, freshman.

290
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:40,417
[HACHIOJI chuckles]
Gion's havin' a rough first day.

291
00:15:42,542 --> 00:15:44,291
[GION]
Oh, yeah. One thing.

292
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:45,709
Why won't that guy join?

293
00:15:45,792 --> 00:15:48,250
The big guy. "Tree trunk."

294
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,375
Sorry! Please don't tackle me!

295
00:15:50,458 --> 00:15:54,291
Oh. Iwashimizu.

296
00:15:55,083 --> 00:15:56,667
Huh?

297
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,959
[HACHIOJI]
Hm...

298
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,250
Well, the truth is...

299
00:16:03,291 --> 00:16:05,750
So, what kinda
books do you like?

300
00:16:05,834 --> 00:16:07,208
Well, I like all kinds,

301
00:16:07,291 --> 00:16:09,750
but lately I've been really
into romance novels.

302
00:16:09,834 --> 00:16:11,750
Yeah! They're the best!

303
00:16:11,834 --> 00:16:12,917
You know something?

304
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,250
At first, we were
pretty scared of you.

305
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:16,792
'Cause you're the biggest
person we've ever seen!

306
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:19,083
But not anymore--we think
you're awesome now!

307
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:21,166
[IWASHIMIZU]
Heh... Thank you?

308
00:16:23,959 --> 00:16:26,458
Uh... Hi, Gion.

309
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:34,792
I need you to come with me, pal!

310
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:40,333
[IWASHIMIZU]
Wait. Do you mean right now?

311
00:16:40,417 --> 00:16:44,500
Because I'd like to, but,
I can't. I have Book Club.

312
00:16:44,583 --> 00:16:47,458
[GION]
Nerd Club's not goin' anywhere.

313
00:16:52,959 --> 00:16:54,375
[GION]
What was he talkin' about?

314
00:16:54,458 --> 00:16:56,125
[IWASHIMIZU]
Uh... Gion?

315
00:16:56,208 --> 00:17:00,917
So, are you gonna tell me
what we're doing out here?

316
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,208
[GION] Oh, is this it?
Dangit, no it's not.

317
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:07,291
This is it! No, false alarm.

318
00:17:07,375 --> 00:17:09,083
Uh... Can I help out?

319
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:12,041
[GION]
It stinks in here!

320
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:13,000
Ah! Jackpot!

321
00:17:13,083 --> 00:17:14,333
[yelps]

322
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:18,834
Why do we need a tackle bag?

323
00:17:18,917 --> 00:17:21,959
[GION] Why do ya think,
tree trunk? For tacklin'.

324
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:25,375
Get ready, dude, cause I'm
about to bring the pain

325
00:17:25,458 --> 00:17:26,834
like you've never seen!

326
00:17:26,917 --> 00:17:28,709
[yelps]

327
00:17:30,083 --> 00:17:31,125
[GION]

328
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:34,166
Just teach me how
to tackle, man! Now!

329
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:35,500
Uh, please?

330
00:17:35,583 --> 00:17:38,500
[HACHIOJI] Hm. It's easy,
you just hurl your body

331
00:17:38,583 --> 00:17:40,083
at your opponent.

332
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:42,959
I'd start off with the tackle
bag in the shed if I were you!

333
00:17:43,041 --> 00:17:46,250
[laughs] You're goin' down, man!

334
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:47,500
[gasps] No.

335
00:17:47,583 --> 00:17:49,583
Please don't do this,
I'm begging you, Gion!

336
00:17:49,667 --> 00:17:51,166
Shut up!

337
00:17:56,583 --> 00:18:00,417
[yells]

338
00:18:02,375 --> 00:18:03,834
[IWASHIMIZU] Most people
are too afraid to charge

339
00:18:03,917 --> 00:18:05,583
at someone when
they first start.

340
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:08,000
But not him--he's fearless.

341
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:20,417
Don't run.

342
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:21,792
[gasps]

343
00:18:22,875 --> 00:18:25,375
[GION]
If you do, you'll get hurt.

344
00:18:28,583 --> 00:18:30,041
[GION]
Gimme that!

345
00:18:34,792 --> 00:18:36,250
Tree trunk. Look.

346
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,291
You tackle me, okay?

347
00:18:38,375 --> 00:18:39,750
Ah! I can't.

348
00:18:39,834 --> 00:18:41,709
No! Don't make me
do this, please!

349
00:18:41,792 --> 00:18:42,792
I'm twice your size!

350
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:45,417
I don't want you
to get hurt, Gion.

351
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:47,208
I won't run away.

352
00:18:47,291 --> 00:18:51,083
I'm gonna hold my ground!
So you can't hurt me!

353
00:18:53,875 --> 00:18:55,458
Come on.

354
00:18:55,542 --> 00:18:58,333
What, are you scared?

355
00:18:58,417 --> 00:19:01,542
Don't be. This isn't
middle school.

356
00:19:11,709 --> 00:19:13,417
[IWASHIMIZU]
Back then, I had a classmate

357
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,709
who was a really
good rugby player.

358
00:19:17,917 --> 00:19:19,917
[IWASHIMIZU] In fact, the only
reason I started playing

359
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,834
in the first place is because
he invited me to join the team.

360
00:19:22,917 --> 00:19:24,250
All right, guys.

361
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:27,583
How 'bout we wrap up practice
with a team scrimmage?

362
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:29,709
[IWASHIMIZU] You're all
pumped up today, aren't ya?

363
00:19:32,375 --> 00:19:33,542
I'm supposed to be!

364
00:19:33,625 --> 00:19:36,041
I am the team captain, right?

365
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:38,166
Besides, man, if we
clean up at the next game,

366
00:19:38,250 --> 00:19:40,542
we're going straight
to Nationals!

367
00:19:40,625 --> 00:19:41,750
[RUGBY PLAYERS grunting]

368
00:19:41,834 --> 00:19:43,500
[RUGBY GUY 1C]
Somebody tackle him already!

369
00:19:46,792 --> 00:19:48,041
[MIYUKI grunts]

370
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,417
[IWASHIMIZU panting]

371
00:19:57,875 --> 00:20:01,208
[MIYUKI screams]

372
00:20:01,291 --> 00:20:01,959
[RUGBY GUY 1A]
What's wrong?

373
00:20:02,041 --> 00:20:02,875
[RUGBY GUY 1B]
Miyuki?

374
00:20:02,959 --> 00:20:03,750
[RUGBY GUY 1C]
Are you okay?

375
00:20:03,834 --> 00:20:06,750
[screaming]

376
00:20:06,834 --> 00:20:07,834
[RUGBY GUY 1A]
Oh, no!

377
00:20:07,917 --> 00:20:08,709
[RUGBY GUY 1B]
Get a teacher!

378
00:20:08,792 --> 00:20:10,083
Someone get a teacher now!

379
00:20:10,166 --> 00:20:12,834
He's in a lot of pain!

380
00:20:12,917 --> 00:20:15,250
[IWASHIMIZU whimpering]

381
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:25,542
[whistle blows]

382
00:20:25,625 --> 00:20:30,250
[GREEN TEAM cheers]

383
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:35,458
[RED TEAM sniffling]

384
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:39,208
[IWASHIMIZU]
Poor Miyuki.

385
00:20:42,041 --> 00:20:44,250
[IWASHIMIZU]
I'm so sorry.

386
00:20:49,375 --> 00:20:51,500
Don't be so cocky.

387
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:53,792
You won't knock my
shoulder out of socket.

388
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:56,291
I can promise you that much!

389
00:20:56,375 --> 00:20:58,417
It's not your fault, okay?

390
00:20:58,500 --> 00:21:01,250
The guy you inured was
just weak, that's all.

391
00:21:02,709 --> 00:21:06,166
[IWASHIMIZU] Don't insult
Miyuki, you understand me?

392
00:21:12,041 --> 00:21:13,834
--[thud]
--[gasps]

393
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:23,959
No. Please.

394
00:21:29,208 --> 00:21:32,375
[pants]

395
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:34,583
[laughing] Ow!

396
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:36,291
Huh?

397
00:21:37,458 --> 00:21:39,083
Dude! Wow!

398
00:21:39,166 --> 00:21:40,542
[gasps]

399
00:21:40,625 --> 00:21:44,291
Nice hit! Rugby is amazing!

400
00:21:50,709 --> 00:21:53,875
[laughs] Oh, man,
you're really huge!

401
00:21:53,959 --> 00:21:57,792
Wanna join the Rugby Team?
You'll love it. Rugby's awesome!

402
00:21:59,709 --> 00:22:02,500
Come on. What do
you have to lose?

403
00:22:10,959 --> 00:22:12,500
[IWASHIMIZU]
Yeah.

404
00:23:44,208 --> 00:23:47,417
[GION] Next time:
"I want to Tackle Someone!"

